<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The friends_timeline method of the Twitter API supports the optional parameters
- since_id.  Optional.  Returns only statuses with an ID greater than (that is, more recent than) the specified ID.  Ex: <a href="http://twitter.com/statuses/friends_timeline.xml?since_id=12345">http://twitter.com/statuses/friends_timeline.xml/…</a>
- count.  Optional.  Specifies the number of statuses to retrieve. May not be greater than 200.  Ex: <a href="http://twitter.com/statuses/friends_timeline.xml?count=5">http://twitter.com/statuses/friends_timeline.xml/…</a></p>

<p>They are not implemented in the statusFriendsTimeline() though.</p>

<p>Additional:
Line 253 of Zend/Service/Twitter.php states:
"     * - id: ID of a friend whose timeline you wish to receive"</p>

<p>Please remove this line completely. This parameter doesn't exist in friends_timeline.</p>

